sequenceDiagram
    title Successful Audit Endpoint Invocation

    actor Client

    box rgb(173, 216, 230) API Layer
    participant AuditEndpoint
    end

    box rgb(144, 238, 144) SATP Business Logic Layer
    participant Dispatcher
    participant AuditHandler
    participant AuditRepository
    end

    box rgb(255, 255, 224) Database Layer
    participant Database
    end

  
    Client->>AuditEndpoint: GET /admin/audit?startTimestamp=...&endTimestamp=...
    Note right of AuditEndpoint: HTTP request with query parameters

    AuditEndpoint->>AuditEndpoint: parseRequiredIso(startTimestamp)
    AuditEndpoint->>AuditEndpoint: parseRequiredIso(endTimestamp)
    AuditEndpoint->>AuditEndpoint: validate(startDate <= endDate)

    AuditEndpoint->>Dispatcher: PerformAudit(auditRequest)
    Note right of Dispatcher: AuditRequest contains start/end timestamps

    Dispatcher->>AuditHandler: executeAudit(logLevel, auditRepository, req)
    AuditHandler->>AuditHandler: getAuditData(logLevel, auditRepository, req)

    AuditHandler->>AuditRepository: readByTimeInterval(startTime, endTime)
    AuditRepository->>Database: SELECT * FROM audit_entries<br/>WHERE timestamp BETWEEN ? AND ?
    Database-->>AuditRepository: audit entries

    AuditRepository-->>AuditHandler: Audit object with entries
    AuditHandler-->>Dispatcher: AuditResponse with entries
    Dispatcher-->>AuditEndpoint: AuditResponse

    AuditEndpoint-->>Client: 200 OK<br/>{<br/>  "auditEntries": {...},<br/>  "startTimestamp": "...",<br/>  "endTimestamp": "..."<br/>}
    Note left of Client: JSON response with audit data
